{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-changelog-js","path":"/changelog/2018/april","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h3 id=\"the-90-day-leaderboard\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#the-90-day-leaderboard\" aria-label=\"the 90 day leaderboard permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The 90 Day Leaderboard</h3>\n<p>The new rolling 90 day leaderboard ranks hackers based on their score from this calculation: <strong>Reputation x Signal Percentile x Impact Percentile</strong>.\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 500px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 31.2%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"april_2018_leaderboard\"\n        title=\"april_2018_leaderboard\"\n        src=\"/static/bbbd115d135d655c3a290abf9476b8fd/0b533/april_2018_leaderboard.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/bbbd115d135d655c3a290abf9476b8fd/fac75/april_2018_leaderboard.png 125w,\n/static/bbbd115d135d655c3a290abf9476b8fd/63868/april_2018_leaderboard.png 250w,\n/static/bbbd115d135d655c3a290abf9476b8fd/0b533/april_2018_leaderboard.png 500w,\n/static/bbbd115d135d655c3a290abf9476b8fd/1d69c/april_2018_leaderboard.png 750w,\n/static/bbbd115d135d655c3a290abf9476b8fd/00d43/april_2018_leaderboard.png 1000w,\n/static/bbbd115d135d655c3a290abf9476b8fd/0c1ff/april_2018_leaderboard.png 2192w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h3 id=\"needs-more-info\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#needs-more-info\" aria-label=\"needs more info permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Needs More Info</h3>\n<p>When a program member adds a comment to an open report with a question mark, Hackbot will prompt them asking if they want to change the state of the report to Needs more info.\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 500px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 32%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"april_2018_nmi\"\n        title=\"april_2018_nmi\"\n        src=\"/static/a1745b5469c4677fe5bd527b3b1bac8b/0b533/april_2018_nmi.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/a1745b5469c4677fe5bd527b3b1bac8b/fac75/april_2018_nmi.png 125w,\n/static/a1745b5469c4677fe5bd527b3b1bac8b/63868/april_2018_nmi.png 250w,\n/static/a1745b5469c4677fe5bd527b3b1bac8b/0b533/april_2018_nmi.png 500w,\n/static/a1745b5469c4677fe5bd527b3b1bac8b/1d69c/april_2018_nmi.png 750w,\n/static/a1745b5469c4677fe5bd527b3b1bac8b/00d43/april_2018_nmi.png 1000w,\n/static/a1745b5469c4677fe5bd527b3b1bac8b/11a8f/april_2018_nmi.png 1272w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<h3 id=\"response-efficiency-timers\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#response-efficiency-timers\" aria-label=\"response efficiency timers permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Response Efficiency Timers</h3>\n<p>Response efficiency timers no longer trigger for reports submitted by internal members of the program. </p>\n<h3 id=\"auto-invites-for-controlled-programs\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#auto-invites-for-controlled-programs\" aria-label=\"auto invites for controlled programs permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Auto-Invites for Controlled Programs</h3>\n<p>Programs in controlled launch mode are no longer able to toggle auto-invites as on or off. To change their settings for invitations, they can contact HackerOne support. </p>\n<h3 id=\"bug-fixes\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#bug-fixes\" aria-label=\"bug fixes permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Bug Fixes</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>URLs in the report title are now wrapped so that they aren’t crossing out of the inbox. </li>\n<li>The Program Health Dashboard now displays 0 instead of N/A when there are no missed or failed reports. </li>\n<li>When a hacker leaves a program that they got invited to through the email forwarding feature, they won’t be placed in the priority queue for leaving that program. This prevents hackers from harvesting a ton of private invitations. </li>\n<li>Hackers now don’t receive invitations to programs they’ve left. </li>\n<li>When hackers received an invitation to claim a report, they couldn’t see or accept the terms of the program. Now they can actually claim the report and see the terms of the program. </li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"path":"/changelog/2018/april","title":"April 2018"}}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":[]}